The paper deals with secure distributed computation, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, given the focus on communication and coding, as well as the use of secure cross subspace alignment (SCSA), it is most likely to be classified under Information Theory (cs.IT). Other possible sub-categories include Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
